The paper proposes a model for sequential prediction in collaborative filtering, which is a task related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The model combines recurrent neural networks and log-bilinear models, which are commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval, suggesting that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.AI. The paper also mentions the use of multiple types of behaviors in historical sequences, which may relate to social networks and recommender systems, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.CL.
